          <td>Depopulation underway</td>
          <td>Roughly 105,000–115,000 policies (late 2025); net count down only ~13% from peak despite ~30,000 sent to private insurers — many owners remain stuck on Citizens. Round 23 depopulation assumes April 2026</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>LDI data shows that Jefferson, Orleans, St. Bernard, and Lafourche parishes have the highest concentration of non-renewal complaints per capita since 2021. Non-renewal and premium increase notices account for the majority of LDI consumer complaints in the 2022 to 2025 period.</p>
  </Fragment>

